Description: Chemguard, Inc is develops and manufactures fire suppression foams, equipment and systems, specialty foam pumps, and fluorosurfactant.
Headquarters Regions: Dallas/Fort Worth Metroplex, Southern US
Full Description: Chemguard serves the fire suppression and specialty chemicals fields worldwide with unmatched customer support, high-quality and field-tested products, and the ability to meet customer requirements through product customization.  ISO 9001:2008 certified, we lead through advanced research, exacting engineering and design, proven manufacturing excellence, and prompt service and delivery.  The Chemguard Fire Suppression Division is a full-service leader in foam concentrates, fire-fighting hardware, and engineered fire-fighting foam systems for industrial, military, municipal, offshore, petrochemical/energy, transportation/freight, and airport hangar applications: We produce the most extensive line of efficient, environmentally friendly, UL Listed and FM Approved fire-fighting foam concentrates in the world, in addition to dry chemicals. Foam blending capability throughout the world enables us to provide prompt delivery, including On Call 24/7 emergency foam shipments. We engineer and manufacturer a broad line of high-quality, durable, and proven fire-fighting hardware, including fixed-system proportioning equipment, discharge devices, portable equipment, a mobile unit, and custom-engineered systems. Our customer support includes foam sample testing, live fire testing, and training. The Chemguard Specialty Chemicals Division – which acquired the LodyneTM fire-fighting fluorosurfactant and foam stabilizers business and the specialty Lodyne™ fluorosurfactant business from Ciba Specialty Chemicals – produces a rapidly expanding selection of fluorosurfactant and hydrocarbon specialty chemical products for wetting/leveling applications and fire-fighting formulations.  Our advanced chemistry, extensive industry knowledge, and prompt delivery enable us to effectively and efficiently meet customers’ requirements for a broad range of applications. Chemguard also manufactures a line of UL Listed and FM Approved positive-displacement foam concentrate pumps for the fire-protection industry.  Constructed from corrosion-resistant brass and stainless steel, the pumps have set new standards for foam concentrate pump performance and reliability.   Chemguard’s comprehensive operation includes chemical manufacturing, dry chemical blending and packaging, foam concentrate blending and packaging, hardware manufacturing, product testing and quality assurance, and bulk chemical storage. We perform ongoing product development and technical support to meet customer requirements and market demands in our state-of-the-art research and development laboratory.

Description: The company plans to build, own and operate a 50 Ton Per Hour (TPH) Construction and Demolition (C&D) (TPH) Material Recovery Facility.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: The company plans to build, own and operate a 50 Ton Per Hour (TPH) Construction and Demolition (C&D) (TPH) Material Recovery Facility (MRF) in Lake County, Illinois. We currently own and operate a 15 TPH recycling facility in Zion, IL., along with a fleet of roll of dumpster rental trucks and power sweeper trucks.     The current operating facility was acquired by the company in October of 2012, by the end of 2012 the facility was over it's processing capacity. In 2013 the company invested in a small conveyor to increase capacity and by the end of summer 2013 the company was again over it processing capacity.     The company has been researching and visiting non-competing facilities for 18 months and has since found a larger, well located facility with a 40,000 square foot existing building on 4 acres of land. The property has been under contract since April 2015 and management has taken the necessary steps to build the new facility including; special use permits, local host agreements, architectural designs and is currently waiting on the Illinois EPA to deliver the development license.     It is our objective to provide local waste haulers, our company included, demolition contractors, businesses, municipalities and homeowners a solution to properly recycle their Construction and Demolition Debris. Our customers will not only save time and money using the facility, but they will be diverting the recyclable debris from local landfills. In addition to the environmental benefits, local municipalities are requiring, through recycling ordinances, that a certain percentage (50%-75% per the local ordinance) of C&D debris be recycled, thus pushing business to our facility.

Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: RockStable uses our stablecoin ROKS to do cross-border money transfers. We initially serve millions of Filipinos working outside the Philippines who regularly send money back home to support their families. The main advantage of our system compared to similar service from Western Union, Remitly, Xoom, Wise, etc is that by using ROKS, we've made it very practical and easy to accept a USD-equivalent in remittances. Using TradFi remittance, it is not practical and not safe for recipients to receive US dollar bills. Depositing the USD to a dollar account in a bank is out of the question because there are only very few people who have USD accounts in banks.  Our ROKS wallet also makes it very easy to cashout ROKS to the local currency and recipients can deposit their local currency to a local wallet app. Wallet apps are very popular in countries like the Philippines where the most popular wallet app, GCash, has at least 65 million users.

Our non-partisan mission is best expressed in our three goals: to serve the nation and the world as the MUSEUM OF WE THE PEOPLE, a national HEADQUARTERS FOR CIVIC EDUCATION, and AMERICA’S TOWN HALL. We illuminate the constitutional debates that affect the lives of all Americans by hosting constitutional conversations on Independence Mall in Philadelphia and across a range of media platforms, and we inspire active citizenship by celebrating the American constitutional tradition. Our three goals can be summarized in three words: VISIT. LEARN. DEBATE. As the Museum of We the People, the Constitution Center features hundreds of interactive exhibits, engaging theatrical performances, and original documents of freedom. As America’s town hall, the National Constitution Center hosts constitutional debates across a range of broadcast and digital media platforms. Full Description: MudBots ™ specializes in 3D Concrete Printing. We are the first company in America to offer concrete printers from small 6’ x 6’ models to large 100’ x 100’ models capable of printing custom homes. MudBots ™ first premiered their line of printers at the 2019 Vegas World of Concrete. MudBots ™ leads the world in 3D concrete printing and has been featured in many magazines all around the world. MudBots is a 3D concrete printing company eager to partner with all industry players from batch plant equipment builders, bag mix suppliers, to additive and chemical companies. MudBots is a proven print platform and the perfect equipment to develop the cement, concrete, and epoxy mixes of the future. Just as the home office printer revolutionized the inkjet cartridge industry, we aim to revolutionize the specialty mud industry. MudBots is the first in the industry to offer a 6’ x 6’ x 5’ Cartesian 3D Printer to aid in the development of specialty concrete mixes. We are excited to offer you a turn-key system consisting of: a work envelope optimized cartesian printer powered by high quality IP65 direct drive NEMA 34 hybrid stepper motors. These motors run in tightly controlled servo loop and is controlled by custom FPGAs and administered by LinuxCNC running on a real-time operating system. These elements combine to form a system with low jerk, high payload, and a repeatability of > 0.1” .
